   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Starting:  <br />
****************************************************<br />
Krayt Dragon Pass, Twilek Advisor, Den of Thieves<br />
<br />
Strategy<br />
****************************************************<br />
This deck is a lot of fun.<br />
<br />
Use Keder the Black to assassinate anyone who becomes a problem.  Since most people have no politics, then you can simply just draw destiny and slaughter whoever you like.  You can also use your Sith in combination to run around and get rid of any key threats that are annoying you.<br />
<br />
Put the Mercenary Pilots into the Patrol Crafts.  They can add destiny and will basically own anyone who tries to fight them.  If you give them Anti-Personnel Cannons then they are even funnier.  <br />
<br />
Den of Thieves can slow down force draining.  Use your Tibanna Gas Miners and Patrol Crafts in the Clouds of Tatooine to get some good force drains out if you don&#39;t feel like attacking people.  If you do though, then just use your Patrol Craft, Sith, and Keder the Blacks to kill whoever you want, wherever you want.<br />
<br />
If your opponent plays a Hidden Base deck then use your Sith Infiltrator to prevent any serious damage from occuring.<br />
<br />
Basically take advantage of the silly little things that cards say and make your opponent lose big in battles. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
